ownedComment.body:
Besides the reference this class can be extended to aggregate one specific features in a group.
A feature can aggregate any static or dynamic road characteristics, e,g, Road Sign information by GDD, specific Road, Section, Lane Characteristics such as ISAD or functional road level, etc.
IMPLEMENTATION NOTE: aggregates VmsStatus, GDD, Traffic Regulation

for Segment and Section only a linear location reference is to be addressed, as this can be done through a location description or by reference to a prefedined linear location specified in a predefined location table a reference to general location is enabled
IMPLEMENTATION NOTE: aggregates VmsStatus, GDD, Traffic Regulation

index which is used for referencing sequential section in a non predefined lane management zone such as in a roadwork
index from 1 to N is used to identify sequential section on the road ora carriageway in the direction of traffic flow

index is used for referencing index from 0 to N is used to address lanes from external carriageway to internal lane
laneNumber specifies the lane according to general location package rule: hardshoukder = 0 lane 1..N regular transitable lanes,
QUESTION: This could be managed linking to traffic regulation reusable class
generic Feature for single features which are not managed as Feature Group
Sections in the segment are indexed by sequence on the road segment in flow direction segment and sections are mono-directional ( positive, negative direction only )
location shall be a network linear location, but a reference to location is used because of possible use of predefined location
Class which can be aggregate also to concrete classes for actual devices such as traffic or weather sensors or vms

index from 0 to N is used to address lanes from external carriageway to internal lane
lane Number: hardshoukder = 0, lane 1..N regular transitable lanes

carriageway and direction shall be referred by the location, they are redundant attributes here but are also the base to identify the segments so they are left for debug and double check immediate information. it's arguable if they should be kept
consider to add allowed manouevres turn left, turn right, u turn,

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Namespace.definition: the modelling of Lane Management in DLM zones and OnTheFly road such as roadworks

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Package.definition: A collection of data and information constructs that are used only in the Lane Management package of the DATEX II model.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: the Feature groups defines a combination of information which is applicable to one or more road elements and can be associated dinamically to them

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: the reference to the feature group

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: a class to reference and eventually associate any possible static or dynamic feature to segments, section and lanes such as road characteristics

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: an external reference to a feature
the referencte to a feature which is may be addressed in the group
the versione reference of a feature which may be addressed in the group

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: defined in traffic regulation model

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Package.definition: A collection of information related to correlate traffic management and traffic restriction configuration which can be applicable to road segments, section and lanes.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: information describing the status of a dynamically managed portion of a carriageway, which can be implemented because of roadworks or any road condition and situation for which a lane transitability is changed with respect to its standard setting.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: when true it specifies the dynamic hardshoulder is managed in the related segmenst and sections

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: A lane homogeneous road portion dynamically managed in a homogenous way

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: the reference to the feature group applied
attribute which define an ordered sequence among he Sections of one Segment, conventionally in the vehicle flow direction
lenght of the section affected
nominal number of lanes in the section
the offset related to the start the section in the flow direction measured from the start of the segment

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: a set of dynamic lane management setting information related to a single road and carriageway/direction

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: indicates the carriageway where the dynamic lane management applies
direction where the dynamic lane management applies
the reference to the feature group applied

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: describes the lane setting

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: if set to True it express the specific lane is dynamically managed, when False it is a static configured lane
the reference to the feature group applied
attribute which define an ordered sequence among the lanes of one section, conventional order is external carriageway towards internal
the lane number
the lane transitability setting
the current usage allowed for the lane (could be managed by reference to general restriction in METR model)
minimum lane width in the current dynamic configuration
it is set to true when the original widgt of the lane in the section is reduces from the designed lane width

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Relation.definition: in a crossway or when merging it specifies the lanes from which the origin lane is merged from
for a deviated lane it express the current location of the deviated lane
in a crossway or in splitting a lane it aggregates any lane to which the lane is splitting to

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: In a crossway or in the dynamically managed carriageway when lanes are merged or splitting, reference to the lanes to or from which the transitability is allowed.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: specifies the index reference related to the referenced section of the segment
specifies the index number of the section in the reference segment
reference to the segment to which the linked lane is related

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: A collection of the individual setting implemented for a dinamic lane management in set of DML managemd Segmnts

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: reference to the Table
the reference to the DLM managed Zone in a predefined Lane Management Table

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: the information related to a specific lane setting, which can be associated to predefined segment and their sections described in a Lane Management Table, or on not predefined sections such as in case of roadworks or a lane regulation for any purposes
the information related to the lane setting

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: the reference to the feature group applied
attribute which define an ordered sequence among the lanes of one section, conventional order is external carriageway towards internal
the status of the lane (open, closed, deviated, etc.)
the lane current usage
minumum width of the lane
it is set to true when the original widgt of the lane in the section is reduces from the designed lane width

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Relation.definition: in a crossway or when merging it specifies the lanes from which the origin lane is merged from
in splitting a lane it aggregates any lane to which the lane is splitting to

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: in a crossway or in the same road when lanes are splitting, defines the lanes to which the transitability from the origin lane is allowed, when not implicit being in the sequence order described by the index

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: specifies the index reference related to the referenced section of the segment
current transitability setting for the connection among lanes (could be replaced by reference to restriction)
specifies the index number of the section in the reference segment
reference to the segment to which the linked lane is related
the current transitability of the link among lane (could be managed by general restriction applied)

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: The information related to a DLM Section

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: express in the homogeneously managed section the effective number of transitable lanes
the reference to the feature group applied
attribute which define an ordered sequence among he Sections of one Segment, conventionally in the vehicle flow direction

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: information describing the setting of a DLM Segment

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: the reference to the feature group applied
if set specifies for hardshoulder running systems the status of hardshoulder transitable
segment reference
the current number nominal of transitable lanes for the segment. The current number of transitable lanes may be less in case of lanes closed or blocked for any reason

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Package.definition: A collection of information related to the dynamic lane management

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: A device which is installed to monitor or manage the segment, section or lane, such as a VMS, a Measurement Site, a Camera, a Traffic Light

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: description of the device
a reference as external identifier to the Device
an identification of a device as reference
an identificaton of the device as versioned reference

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: Indicates a specific lane which can be regular or transitional ( i.e. splitting or merging lane) which transitability can be regulated by means of static signs or Variable Message Signs, such as Lane Control Signs (LCS)

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: when set to True express the specific lane is dynamically managed, when False it is a static configured lane
the reference to the feature group applied to the lane
attribute which define an ordered sequence the lanes of one section, conventional order is external bound to internal as laneNumber attribute which may overlap with this
The number of the lane, where 1 is nearest the hard shoulder/verge and the numbers increase towards the central reservation/road axis.
Indicates the standard usage for lane
minimum width of the lane
can be used for vehicle in both direction based on setting
lane which is splitting in 2 lanes or merging from 2 lanes in this section
for transitional lanes indicates the splitting or meging transition of the specific lane

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Relation.definition: in a crossway or when merging it specifies the lanes from which the origin lane is merged from
in splitting a lane it aggregates any lane to which the lane is splitting to

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2VersionedIden.definition: A versioned Dynamic Lane Management (DML) Table comprising a number of road zones divided in segments wher DLM management is in place by means of devices /signs which allow the DML management itself

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: A string used as identification of the table by Traffic Operators

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: Besides implicit connections in the sequence order described by indexes in sequencial sections, the reference to a linked lane in a crossway or in the same road when lane is merging or splitting

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: specifies the index reference related to the referenced section of the segment
specifies the index number of the section in the reference segment
reference to the segment to which the linked lane is related

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: holds the reference to the linked segment, to or from which the associated segment drives

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: reference to the linked segment

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Relation.definition: When segment ends into another one it express the segment to which the original segment is connected
When segment goes on from another one it express the segment from which the original segment is going on

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: Section of Road which has homogeneous lane management by regulation, optionally implemented by Lane Control Systems signs or static signs or other devices.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: the reference to the feature group applied to the section
attribute which define an ordered sequence among he Sections of one Segment, conventionally in the vehicle flow direction
extension lenght of the section
numer of transitable lanes in normal conditions (hardshoulder considered as not transitable)
the offset of the beginning of the section measured from the start of the segment

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2VersionedIden.definition: A continuous portion of road where lanes are uniformely managed by means of Dynamic Lane Management regulations, signs or devices, divided in homogeneous lanes and devices Sections

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: specifies the carriageway related to the segment
direction of the segment
the reference to the feature group applied to the segment
lenght extension of the segment

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2VersionedIden.definition: A continuous road portion, divided in one or more segment, where Dynamic Lane Management is done through specific regulations, signs and/or devices.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: when true it specifies the dynamic hardshoulder is managed in the zone
if true it specifies a dynamic lane is managed for the zone and within its Segments and Sections
the reference to the feature group applied to the zone
a reference string which is used to identify the zone by the operators
a geographical or network conventional name for the zone (e.g. "Milan ring road")

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Package.definition: A collection of information related to static lane description which enable dynamic lane management in predefined road zones, eventually by means of specific devices, such as static Signs and VMS.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Enumeration.definition: Setting status of lanes by the responsible authority based on standardised regulation

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Literal.definition: the lane is being used for alternate circulation in both directions
the lane is closed to all vehicles in any directions
the lane is being deviated to left, vehicle should move to the lane immediately at lane left
the lane is being deviated to right, vehicle should move to the lane immediately at lane right
the lane is open, vehicles may be allowed to circulate oir not based on other specific regulation
the lane is being used by circulating traffic in the opposed direction than the standard circulation rules

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Enumeration.definition: conventional transition considered for a lane when merging and splitting

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Literal.definition: merging lane from 2 (..n) lanes into 1 lane, direction to not evident or significant
merging lane from 2 (..n) lanes into 1 lane to left
merging lane from 2 (..n) lanes into 1 lane to Right
splitting from 1 lane into 2 (..n) lanes, direction splitting not significant or evident
splitting from1 lane into 2 (..n) lanes to left
splitting from 1 lane into 2 (..n) lanes to right

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Package.definition: A collection of enumerations that are used only in the LaneManagement package of the DATEX II model.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: A publication containing zero or more Lane Management setting description

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Package.definition: A collection of information related to the Publication of Lane Management information

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: A publication containing one or more Lane Management Tables each comprising a set of records which hold details of how the Lane Management segments and sections are defined.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2ModelRoot.definition: A publication containing one or more Lane Management Tables each comprising a set of records which hold details of how the Lane Management segments and sections are defined.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Package.definition: A collection of data relating to the publication of lane management information.

tag.name: definition
tag.value: When segment goes on from another one it express the segment from which the original segment is going on
